<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT - Microsoft lowered.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - Microsoft lowered.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-06-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Furman Selz said analyst Sanjiv Hingoram removed Microsoft Corp from the firm's recommended list, lowering it to neutral from buy.</p>
<p>-- in a report, the analyst cited the stock's valuation, noting it was trading at price/earnings multiples of 42 times his fiscal 1998 estimate and 33.6 times his 1999 view.</p>
<p>-- said &quot;we believe that Microsoft's ability to provide meaningful upside surprises to published EPS estimates for fiscal 1998 may be lower than in recent prior periods because of the absence of a major product cycle in fiscal 1998.&quot;</p>
<p>-- the stock was off 1-4/16 to 128-15/16</p>
